Really friendly place and good food overall.
I ordered the baked ziti and it was just how I like it.
I'm not a huge fan of any red sauce but they mix in a lot of cheeses which gives it more of a blended flavor.
Usually when I see "baked" and "pasta" I expect a soft, mushy mess, but the ziti had a lot of firmness to it which is what I want.
I didn't get around to eating the garlic bread until an hour after I ordered and I was expecting a brick, but somehow it managed to say soft.
Nice bonus.
I got a slice as well to try it out.
They serve thin pizza, but I'm more of a thick crust person, but it was good overall.
The crumbled sausage is just what I like.
The staff was friendly and they seemed to be enjoying themselves.
Nice place to take a family.

