Nope.
I emailed GrubHub, they said they spoke with Stumpy's and the missing items were on their way.
Well nothing ever showed up, the restaurant never refunded our money for the missing items and GrubHub shrugged it off with a "we're sorry, here's $5 off your next order" canned reply.
That was a fraction of the value of the items we were shorted.
This fly-by-night service is DOA in my book.
